Database Server Benchmark: Sysbench
(http://www.howtoforge.com/how-to-benchmark-your-system-cpu-file-io-mysql-with-sysbench)

Installation:

1. Install Mysql server:
	sudo aptitude update
	sudo aptitude install mysql-server

2. Launch Mysql:
	sudo service mysql start

3. Enter Mysql shell:
	/usr/bin/mysql -u root -p

4. Create database:
	CREATE DATABASE demodb;

5. Check database:
	SHOW DATABASES;

6. Quite Mysql shell:
	quit

7. Install Sysbench:
	apt-get install sysbench

8. Create table:
	sysbench --test=oltp --oltp-table-size=1000000 --mysql-db=test --mysql-user=root --mysql-password=yourrootsqlpassword prepare

9. Run test:
	sysbench --test=oltp --oltp-table-size=1000000 --mysql-db=test --mysql-user=root --mysql-password=yourrootsqlpassword --max-time=60 --oltp-read-only=on --max-requests=0 --num-threads=128 run

10. Clean up the table:
	sysbench --test=oltp --mysql-db=test --mysql-user=root --mysql-password=yourrootsqlpassword cleanup
